quran[52]{c,v,t}:
  69,1,The Haqqah
  69,2,What is the Haqqah
  69,3,And what will make you understand what the Haqqah is
  69,4,The Thamud and the ‘Ad people denied the striking calamity
  69,5,"As for Thamud, they were destroyed by the Thunderbolt"
  69,6,As for 'Ad they were destroyed by a furious windstorm
  69,7,"which He let loose on them for seven nights and eight successive days. Had you been there, you would have seen them lying prostrate as though they were hollow trunks of the palm-trees"
  69,8,"Now, do you see any of them alive"
  69,9,"Pharaoh and those before him, and the inhabitants of the overthrown cities also committed similar sins"
  69,10,"and disobeyed the Messengers of their Lord, so He gripped them with a tight grip"
  69,11,"Just consider the great flood of Noah, when the water rose high, We carried you (O mankind) in the floating Ark"
  69,12,that We may make that event a warning for you so that all attentive ears may retain its memory
  69,13,"As for the dooms- day, it shall come, when the Trumpet will be blown with a single blast"
  69,14,and the earth with all its mountains will be lifted up and crushed into pieces with a single stroke
  69,15,On that day the Great Event will come to pass
  69,16,"heaven shall split asunder, and the day shall seem flimsy"
  69,17,The angels will stand all around and eight of them will be carrying the Throne of your Lord above them
  69,18,"That shall be the day when you will be brought before your Lord, and none of your secrets shall remain hidden"
  69,19,"Then he, who will be given his Book of Deeds in his right hand, will say: \"Here it is, read my Book of deeds"
  69,20,I knew that I would certainly face my reckoning
  69,21,So he will have a life of pleasure
  69,22,in a lofty garden
  69,23,with clusters of fruit within his reach
  69,24,"We shall say to him: \"Eat and drink to your heart's content; this is a reward for what you did in the days gone by"
  69,25,"While he, who will be given his Book of Deeds in his left hand, will say: \"Woe to me, would that I had not been given my Book of Deeds"
  69,26,nor known what my account was
  69,27,Would that my death had ended all
  69,28,My wealth had availed me nothing
  69,29,and my authority has gone away from me
  69,30,"We shall say: \"Seize him and put a chain around his neck"
  69,31,then cast him in the blazing fire
  69,32,then fasten him with a chain seventy cubits long
  69,33,"For he did not believe in Allah, the Most High"
  69,34,nor did he care to feed the poor
  69,35,Today he neither has a true friend here
  69,36,nor any food except the pus from the washing of wounds
  69,37,which none but the wrongdoers eat
  69,38,Nay! I swear by all that you can see
  69,39,and all that you cannot see
  69,40,that this is the word of a noble Messenger
  69,41,It is not the word of a poet - little is it that you believe
  69,42,nor is it the word of a soothsayer - little admonition is that you take
  69,43,This is a revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  69,44,Had he (Muhammad) invented false statements concerning Us
  69,45,We would certainly have seized him by his right hand
  69,46,then cut off his main artery
  69,47,and none of you could prevent it
  69,48,Surely this Qur’an is a reminder to the Godfearing
  69,49,We know that there are some among you who deny it
  69,50,and for such disbelievers it is indeed a cause of despair
  69,51,Yet surely it is the absolute truth
  69,52,"So glorify the name of your Lord, the Most High"